{{Infobox mountain pass | name = Col Ferret | photo = | photo_caption = | elevation_m = 2490 | elevation_ref = | traversed = Trail | location = [[Italy]]–[[Switzerland]] border | range = [[Alps]] | coordinates = {{coord|45|53|55|N|07|04|06|E|type:pass_region:CH|display=inline,title}} | topo = }}
The '''Col Ferret''' (''Petit Col Ferret'') (el. 2490 m.) is an [[Alps|Alpine]] pass between the canton of [[Valais]] and the [[Aosta Valley]]. This pass separates the [[Mont Blanc Massif]] from the [[Pennine Alps]].
