[[Image:Leti.png|thumb|upright=1.20|Map of Maluku archipelago. Leti is located in southwestern part of the archipelago.]] [[File:Leti Islands en.png|thumbnail]]
'''Leti''' is an [[Indonesia]]n island, the westernmost of the [[Leti Islands]], and one of the 92 officially listed [[List of outlying islands of Indonesia|outlying islands of Indonesia]]. Leti is located in southwest [[Maluku (province)|Maluku]] [[Provinces of Indonesia|province]]. The main town is [[Sewaru]].
The [[Leti language]], a member of [[Austronesian languages]] is spoken on Leti.
